Arsene Wenger believes the strong British core of his current Arsenal squad will ensure the team does not break-up.

Having ended their trophy drought against today’s opponents Hull City in last year’s FA Cup final, there is a belief the Gunners can go on to emulate some of Wenger’s previously successful sides.

Over the years Arsenal have begrudgingly allowed their top stars move to rival clubs; the likes of Cesc Fabregas, Bacary Sagna, Samir Nasri, Gael Clichy and Robin van Persie have all left the Emirates Stadium in recent seasons despite the Wenger’s attempts to keep them.

