Five Arsenal players - Wilshere, Welbeck, Oxlade-Chamberlain, Kieran Gibbs and Calum Chambers - played for England in the European Championship qualifier against Estonia on Sunday.

And Wenger added: ‘I am very proud of that because for years I have been accused of not developing English players.

‘It shows you, when they are good, they play. In a good class you become better. That shows the good players will learn.’

 

